# Optional few-shot voice examples appended to the system prompt.
# Copy this file to `examples.txt` and paste in real conversation excerpts that
# capture the tone/cadence you want the bot to mimic.
#
# Rules:
#   - Lines starting with `#` are stripped as comments.
#   - Everything else is passed through mostly as-is; the loader auto-strips
#     Discord chrome (bracketed timestamps like `[4:59 PM]` and `(edited)`
#     markers) so raw copy-paste from Discord works.
#   - Re-read every generation, so edits take effect on the next reply without
#     a bot restart.
#   - Set `EXAMPLES_PATH = None` (or "") in config.py to disable entirely.
#
# Format is flexible. Anything Discord-shaped works, e.g.:
#
#   alice: this game is dogshit
#   bob: yeah i uninstalled
#   khronic: it was never gonna be good
#
# Or raw copy-paste including usernames and role tags:
#
#   [4:59 PM]alice [FMHY], :
#   this game is dogshit
#   [5:00 PM]bob:
#   yeah i uninstalled
